        <updateDate>2011-06-23T14:57:29Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Empowering More Productive and Lasting Opportunity Act of 2011 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow states, for a five-year period, to implement an employment assistance voucher program, in lieu of paying unemployment compensation directly to e<o>mployees, under which an individual who is eligible for unemployment compensation and is likely to exhaust such compensation is issued an employment assistance voucher and is hired by a participating employer who receives a subsidy from the state for the wages paid to the employee.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
